  • Classes in org.neo4j.index.internal.gbptree used by org.neo4j.consistency.internal

    RecoveryCleanupWorkCollector

  • Classes in org.neo4j.index.internal.gbptree used by org.neo4j.index.internal.gbptree 
    Class Description
    CleanupJob
    A job cleaning something up after recovery.
    CleanupJob.Executor
    Executor of asynchronous units of work needed during the recovery clean up.
    CleanupJob.JobResult
    Result handle of jobs executed by CleanupJob.Executor.
    CrashGenerationCleaner
    Scans the entire tree and checks all GSPPs, replacing all CRASH gen GSPs with zeros.
    DynamicSizeOffsetFormat
    Depending on page size TreeNodeDynamicSize need a various number of bytes to encode the offsets in offset array and for the various meta-data in the header.
    FreeListIdProvider  
    FreeListIdProvider.Monitor  
    FreelistNode
    Manages the physical format of a free-list node, i.e. how bytes about free-list pages are represented out in PageCursor.
    GBPTree
    A generation-aware B+tree (GB+Tree) implementation directly atop a PageCache with no caching in between.
    GBPTree.Monitor
    For monitoring GBPTree.
    GBPTree.SingleWriter  
    GBPTreeBootstrapper.Bootstrap  
    GBPTreeBootstrapper.MetaVisitor  
    GBPTreeBootstrapper.StateVisitor  
    GBPTreeConsistencyChecker.DelayedVisitor.KeyInWrongNode  
    GBPTreeConsistencyCheckVisitor
    The @Documented annotations are used for error messages in consistency checker.
    GBPTreeConsistencyCheckVisitor.Adaptor  
    GBPTreeGenerationTarget  
    GBPTreeInspection  
    GBPTreeLock  
    GBPTreePointerType  
    GBPTreePointerType.SimplePointer  
    GBPTreeUnsafe  
    GBPTreeVisitor  
    GBPTreeVisitor.Adaptor  
    GenerationKeeper
    GBPTreeGenerationTarget which has its own generation field.
    Header.Reader
    Reads a header from a GBPTree state page during opening it.
    Header.Writer
    Writes a header into a GBPTree state page during GBPTree.checkpoint(IOLimiter, PageCursorTracer).
    IdProvider
    Provide tree node (page) ids which can be used for storing tree node data.
    IdProvider.IdProviderVisitor  
    InspectingVisitor.FreelistEntry  
    InternalTreeLogic
    Implementation of GB+ tree insert/remove algorithms.
    InternalTreeLogic.Level
    Keeps information about one level in a path down the tree where the PageCursor is currently at.
    KeyRange  
    Layout
    Main point of interaction for customizing a GBPTree, how its keys and values are represented as bytes and what keys and values contains.
    LayoutBootstrapper  
    Meta
    About versioning (i.e. the format version int): The format version started out as one int controlling the entire version of the tree and its different types of formats.
    MetadataMismatchException
    Thrown to signal mismatches between meta data about tree and user-provided configuration.
    OffloadIdValidator  
    OffloadPageCursorFactory
    This interface exists so that OffloadStoreImpl can be used in GBPTree tests that are not backed by a page cache but rather by ByteArrayPageCursor.
    OffloadStore
    Store used by TreeNodeDynamicSize to store keys and values that are too large to be inlined in GBPTree.
    OffloadStoreImpl
    Offload page layout: [HEADER 9B| KEYSIZE 4B| VALUESIZE 4B | KEY | VALUE] [HEADER]: [TYPE 1B | RESERVED SPACE 8B] Key and value size are simple integers Key and value layout is decided by layout.
    PrintConfig  
    RecoveryCleanupWorkCollector
    Place to add recovery cleanup work to be done as part of recovery of GBPTree.
    RecoveryCleanupWorkCollector.CleanupJobGroupAction  
    RecoveryCleanupWorkCollector.IgnoringRecoveryCleanupWorkCollector
    RecoveryCleanupWorkCollector ignoring all CleanupJob added to it.
    RecoveryCleanupWorkCollector.ImmediateRecoveryCleanupWorkCollector
    RecoveryCleanupWorkCollector which runs added CleanupJob as part of the RecoveryCleanupWorkCollector.ImmediateRecoveryCleanupWorkCollector.add(CleanupJob) call in the caller thread.
    RightmostInChain
    Used to verify a chain of siblings starting with leftmost node.
    Root
    Keeps id and generation of root of the tree.
    RootCatchup  
    SeekCursor.Monitor  
    SeekCursor.MonitorAdaptor  
    Seeker
    Seeks and allows read access to data in a GBPTree.
    Seeker.Factory  
    SizeEstimationMonitor.Stats  
    StructurePropagation
    Means of communicating information about splits, caused by insertion, from lower levels of the tree up to parent and potentially all the way up to the root.
    StructurePropagation.KeyReplaceStrategy  
    StructurePropagation.StructureUpdate  
    TreeNode
    Methods to manipulate single tree node such as set and get header fields, insert and fetch keys, values and children.
    TreeNode.Overflow  
    TreeNode.Type  
    TreeNodeSelector.Factory
    Able to instantiate TreeNode of a specific format and version.
    TreeState
    Tree state is defined as top level tree meta data which changes as the tree and its constructs changes, such as: stable/unstable generation numbers root id, the page id containing the root of the tree last id, the page id which is the highest allocated in the store pointers into free-list (page id + offset) This class also knows how to write and read tree state to and from a PageCursor, although doesn't care where in the store that is.
    ValueMerger
    Decides what to do when inserting key which already exists in index.
    ValueMerger.MergeResult
    Result of a merge, i.e. what the (mutable) values passed into ValueMerger.merge(Object, Object, Object, Object) mean when the call is completed.
    Writer
    Able to Writer.merge(Object, Object, ValueMerger) and Writer.remove(Object) key/value pairs into a GBPTree.
